<!-- ============================== 10. KNOWN GAPS ============================== -->
<h2>10. Known Gaps, Risks, and Recommendations</h2>

<h3>10.1 Functional gaps (from <code>docs/audits/2026-05-18-functional-audit.md</code>)</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Sev</th><th>Issue</th><th>Where</th></tr>
<tr><td>P1</td><td><code>/submit</code> hard-codes <code>http://localhost:5400</code></td><td><code>src/frontend/src/app/submit/page.tsx:20</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td><code>/api/translate</code> silently returns 503 when both ANTHROPIC and DEEPSEEK keys are absent</td><td><code>api/main.py:436</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td><code>/api/discovery/discover-news</code> hard-400 when PERPLEXITY_API_KEY unset; anon-IP rate-limit bypasses tier accounting</td><td><code>api/discovery_routes.py:168&ndash;184</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td>methodology/hallucination-rates joins <code>articles.id</code> (schema uses <code>article_id</code>) &rarr; everything buckets as &ldquo;unknown&rdquo;</td><td><code>api/methodology_routes.py:655</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td><code>/api/methodology/indicators</code> silently returns empty when indicator migrations not applied</td><td><code>api/methodology_routes.py:206&ndash;243</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td>legacy <code>overall_green_score</code> is article-count proxy; mitigated by caveat but UI must surface it</td><td><code>api/green_transition_routes.py:117&ndash;147</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td><code>/api/scheduler/*</code> returns <code>status="skipped"</code> on ImportError; Cloud Scheduler reports 200 OK on dead pipeline</td><td><code>api/scheduler_routes.py:72&ndash;172</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td><code>/api/research/analyze</code> returns 500 on any failure without distinguishing PDF/DOI/LLM error</td><td><code>api/research_routes.py:31&ndash;66</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>P2</td><td>calibration refit returns <code>insufficient_data</code> but no UI to enter labels from <code>/methodology</code></td><td><code>api/methodology_routes.py:450&ndash;470</code></td></tr>
</table>

<h3>10.2 UI/UX gaps (from <code>docs/audits/2026-05-18-uiux-audit.md</code>)</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>P1 &mdash;</b> Chat is read-only / answer-only; cannot drive the platform. Action protocol required (see &sect;8.8).</li>
  <li><b>P1 &mdash;</b> <code>/feed</code> hard-codes 33 countries vs the platform&rsquo;s advertised 198-country coverage.</li>
  <li><b>P1 &mdash;</b> <code>/search</code> falls back to plain text spinner while <code>/</code> uses skeletons &mdash;
      inconsistent across the two most-used pages.</li>
  <li><b>P1 &mdash;</b> Dark-mode tokens on the home page produce light-on-light when the theme toggles.</li>
  <li><b>P2 &mdash;</b> Accessibility: icon-only buttons (theme toggle, remove-bookmark, view-mode) lack
      <code>aria-label</code>s.</li>
  <li><b>P2 &mdash;</b> Article detail page has no <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> landmark.</li>
  <li><b>P3 &mdash;</b> Nav hides on <code>/articles/*</code>, <code>/dashboard/*</code>, etc.; standalone pages have no
      navigation back.</li>
</ul>

<h3>10.3 Analytical gaps (from <code>docs/audits/2026-05-18-analytical-audit.md</code>)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>ND-GAIN fetched but unused in the sustainability composite.</li>
  <li>Calibration <code>min_labels=5</code> too low for stable Platt scaling.</li>
  <li>Venue whitelist of 8 publishers is the entire source-tiering apparatus.</li>
  <li>Multi-LLM shared-prompt design collapses model independence; numeric grounding against indicators not enforced.</li>
  <li>Mixed-year indicator inputs blended into one score without confidence-band widening.</li>
  <li>Drift thresholds hard-coded; 30-day baseline too short for a new platform.</li>
  <li>Hallucination entity check is regex on capitalised n-grams (over-flags numeric synthesis, under-flags entity
      hallucination).</li>
</ul>

<h3>10.4 Data-integrity gaps</h3>
<ul>
  <li>3,588 synthetic seed articles still surfaced on the map, search and compare frontends (migration 025 added the
      flag; frontend filter is the pending follow-up).</li>
  <li>RSS adapter persists summaries rather than article bodies &mdash; the entire downstream chain operates on stubs.</li>
</ul>

<h3>10.5 Recommended next-sprint shape</h3>
<ol>
  <li><b>Hardening + data integrity (1 week).</b> Ship RSS full-body extraction (trafilatura), filter synthetic flag on
      frontends, fix the <code>articles.id</code> &harr; <code>article_id</code> bug in hallucination-rates, harden
      <code>/api/scheduler/*</code> failure modes.</li>
  <li><b>Sustainability v2 + calibration honesty (3&ndash;4 days).</b> ND-GAIN into composite; year_spread band-widening;
      min_labels=50 with preview tag; n_labels surfaced on <code>/api/methodology/calibration</code>.</li>
  <li><b>Sprint A &mdash; coverage RSS packs (1 week).</b> Pacific SIDS, francophone Africa, Caribbean, Central America,
      Central Asia. Adds ~38 countries.</li>
  <li><b>Agentic chat actions (1 week).</b> Backend <code>actions</code> payload + client dispatchers for the 8 top
      intent types from &sect;8.8.</li>
  <li><b>S5 httpOnly cookie migration (4&ndash;6 hours when ready to commit a focused chunk).</b></li>
</ol>

<!-- ============================== 11. GLOSSARY ============================== -->
<h2>11. Glossary &amp; Reference</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Term</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td>CARF</td><td>Causal Analytical Reasoning Framework &mdash; optional external HTTP reasoning engine; fallback is the Cynefin keyword classifier.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cynefin</td><td>Sense-making framework used to route claims between simple / complicated / complex / chaotic reasoning paths.</td></tr>
<tr><td>HybridRAG</td><td>Composed retrieval over FTS + pgvector + knowledge graph, pre-routed by a Cynefin classifier.</td></tr>
<tr><td>HNSW</td><td>Hierarchical Navigable Small World &mdash; the pgvector ANN index used for embedding similarity.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Platt scaling</td><td>Two-parameter logistic regression that maps raw model confidences to calibrated probabilities.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Brier / ECE</td><td>Brier score and Expected Calibration Error &mdash; the two scalar metrics surfaced for each calibration fit.</td></tr>
<tr><td>KL divergence</td><td>Information-theoretic distance between probability distributions; used for drift detection on source mix and prompt fingerprint.</td></tr>
<tr><td>ND-GAIN</td><td>Notre Dame Global Adaptation Index &mdash; country adaptation readiness score.</td></tr>
<tr><td>CAT</td><td>Climate Action Tracker &mdash; 5-band per-country policy rating mapped to 0&ndash;100.</td></tr>
<tr><td>OWID</td><td>Our World in Data &mdash; CSV-distributed canonical climate datasets.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Claim provenance</td><td>The audit table that records model + prompt + version + fingerprint + retrieval strategy + source IDs + hallucination score for every LLM-producing step.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Methodology version</td><td>Pinned identifier (e.g. <code>sustainability_v1_2026_05</code>) attached to every analytical output so historical scores remain reproducible after formula changes.</td></tr>
</table>

<p class=subtle>This report consolidates the codebase, the project memory index, and the seven audits dated 2026-05-18
(analytical, functional, UI/UX, performance, data sources, security, projectcarfcynepic comparison). For deeper drill-down
on any section see the referenced source files and audit documents under <code>docs/audits/</code>.</p>

